entries.title: Idaho murders: Suspect was identified through DNA using genealogy databases
entries.description: The suspect accused of murdering four University of Idaho students in November was identified through DNA using public genealogy databases.

entries.title: National park closes after hundreds of migrants land on islands
entries.description: Dry Tortugas National Park announced it would close on Monday after multiple migrant landings over the past couple of days shut down operations at the park.

entries.title: 6 die in 3-vehicle crash on Texas highway, authorities say
entries.description: Authorities say a three-car crash in southern Texas has killed six people and injured five others

entries.title: House GOP promises to probe COVID-19 origins, ax proxy voting, magnetometers
entries.description: House GOP promises to probe COVID-19 origins, ax proxy voting, magnetometers.

entries.title: Suspect charged in New Year's Eve machete attack on police officers near Times Square
entries.description: Trevor Bickford faces two charges of attempted murder of a police officer.

entries.title: 3 dead, 2 hurt in North Carolina construction site accident
entries.description: Authorities say three construction workers were killed and two others were hurt when scaffolding collapsed in an industrial accident at a job site in Charlotte, North Carolina

entries.title: Tennis legend Martina Navratilova diagnosed with throat, breast cancer
entries.description: Tennis legend Martina Navratilova announced Monday she is suffering from throat cancer, as well as a recurrence of breast cancer.

entries.title: US may execute its first openly transgender woman
entries.description: Unless Missouri Gov. Mike Parson grants clemency, Amber McLaughlin will become the first openly transgender woman executed in the U.S. She is scheduled to die by injection Tuesday for killing a former girlfriend in 2003

entries.title: NYC nurses, hospitals resume contract talks; some reach pact
entries.description: A possible strike by thousands of New York City nurses is looming even though nurses at one hospital reached a tentative agreement hours before their contract was set to expire

entries.title: 300 migrants make landings at national park in Florida Keys
entries.description: A U.S. national park comprising a cluster of uninhabited islands in the Florida Keys has been closed after 300 migrants made 10 landings there over the weekend

entries.title: Suspected gas blast levels 2 homes, hurts 5 in Philadelphia
entries.description: A suspected gas explosion a few hours into the new year demolished two Philadelphia row homes and sent several people to the hospital

entries.title: Greece: Baby's body found in dam; mother arrested
entries.description: A 29-year-old woman has been arrested in connection with the death of her baby daughter in northern Greece

entries.title: Floods in Philippines leave 51 dead, over a dozen missing
entries.description: The death toll in the massive floods that devastated parts of the Philippines over the Christmas weekend has climbed to 51, with 19 others missing

entries.title: Police: Gunmen attack Kashmir village, killing 4 civilians
entries.description: Assailants sprayed bullets toward a row of civilian homes in a remote village in Indian-controlled Kashmir leaving at least four civilians dead and five others injured

entries.title: Israeli army kills 2 Palestinians in West Bank confrontation
entries.description: Palestinian health officials say Israeli forces have killed two Palestinians during a confrontation that erupted when troops entered a village in the occupied West Bank

entries.title: Israeli missile strikes put Damascus airport out of service
entries.description: The Syrian army says missile strikes by Israel’s military have put the capital's airport out of service

entries.title: Actor Jeremy Renner in ‘critical but stable condition’ after snow plow accident
entries.description: Actor Jeremy Renner was injured while plowing snow on Monday, leaving him in “critical but stable condition,” according to his publicist.

entries.title: Jeremy Renner hospitalized after snow-related accident
entries.description: “Avengers” star Jeremy Renner is being treated for serious injuries that happened while he was plowing snow

entries.title: Helicopters collide over Australian beach, passengers hurt
entries.description: Two helicopters collided Monday over an Australian beach and passengers in one of the aircraft were injured

entries.title: 1 person found dead in flooded car as California county faces floodwaters
entries.description: One person was found dead in their vehicle in California on Sunday morning, as a winter storm brought flooding and heavy snow to the state.
